                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14595531" author="rosu" created="Mon, 22 Jun 2015 08:58:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added test &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14595559" author="rosu" created="Mon, 22 Jun 2015 09:14:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;currently a query with UNION and LIMIT applies the same limit to left and right subqueries&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if the left and right subqueries have, for example, the same results then the number of results after the union is limit&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;applying offset to this will result in less results &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;solution: limit left and right subquery to (limit+offset)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
